.TH wxPickerBase 3 "wx 2.5.4" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
wxPickerBase \- Base abstract class for all pickers which support an auxiliary text control.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This class handles all positioning and sizing of the text control like a an horizontal \fIwxBoxSizer\fR would do, with the text control on the left of the picker button.

.PP
The proportion (see \fIwxSizer\fR documentation for more info about proportion values) of the picker control defaults to 1 when there isn't a text control associated (see \fIwxPB_USE_TEXTCTRL\fR style) and to 0 otherwise.

.SS "Styles"

.PP
This class supports the following styles:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxPB_USE_TEXTCTRL: Creates a text control to the left of the picker which is completely managed by this \fIwxPickerBase\fR class.

.RE

.PP
See: \fIwxColourPickerCtrl\fR

.PP
This class is derived, and can use functions, from:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxControl\fR

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxWindow\fR

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxEvtHandler\fR

.RE

